communications.subject: Tennessee Public Records Act Request: Chimneyrock Elementary Good News Club
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Tennessee Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Receipts and/or invoices and/or transaction information and/or emails related to Child Evangelism Fellowship and/or the Good New Club payment for facility use fee and/or facility rental fee from January 2022 to present day, emails related to Child Evangelism Fellowship and/or the Good New Club operating at Chimneyrock Elementary from January 2022 to present day, and documents, texts, emails with the keywords "Good News Club" and/or "GNC" and/or "Child Evangelism Fellowship" and/or "CEF" and/or "Satan" from January 2022 to present day.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 7 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Kent Hoover, a citizen of Tennessee, in coordination with Rachel Janes.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 3 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Jeremy Jong

title: Orleans Parish District Attorney- Louisiana Attorney General Agreement

communications.subject: Louisiana Public Records Law Request: Orleans Parish District Attorney- Louisiana Attorney General Agreement
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Louisiana Public Records Law, I hereby request the following records:

All agreements and contracts between the Orleans Parish District Attorney and the Louisiana Attorney General concerning the partnership between the two offices detailed in the November 29, 2023 press conference attended by DA Jason Williams and AG elect Liz Murrill. An article about the press conference is attached.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 3 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Jeremy Jong
